<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Hugo on knowledge base</title><link>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/tags/hugo/</link><description>Recent content in Hugo on knowledge base</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 15 Aug 2021 07:21:07 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kbs.murarisumit.in/tags/hugo/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Cross Referencing Hugo</title><link>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/a8aa80afb3e281cf2246df975fef9aa8/</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 Aug 2021 07:21:07 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/a8aa80afb3e281cf2246df975fef9aa8/</guid><description>&lt;p>In my blog, have started to cross-refernce now. Hugo has got support for this and designed in such a way that really make sense to me.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Documentation for this is here: &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/content-management/cross-references/">https://gohugo.io/content-management/cross-references/&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So to reference some post, you need to know about &lt;strong>file path of that post&lt;/strong>. Proper reading would have made it easier but spent around 2hrs for this stupid things.&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>The ref and relref shortcodes require a single parameter: the path to a content document, with or without a file extension, with or without an anchor.&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>Instead of &lt;strong>filepath&lt;/strong> went along with URL of the output file, and wasted all effort there, did all I could and later to realise that linking by URL doesn&amp;rsquo;t even make sense, path makes sense. Even if tomorrow you can permalink style, it won&amp;rsquo;t impact your reference link in hugo.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>{{&amp;lt; ref &amp;quot;path-to-file.md&amp;quot; &amp;gt;}}&lt;/code> or &lt;code>{{&amp;lt; ref &amp;quot;path-to-file&amp;quot; &amp;gt;}}&lt;/code> both work fine&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So for anchor tags: &lt;code>[text]({{&amp;lt; ref &amp;quot;path-to-file&amp;quot; &amp;gt;}})&lt;/code>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hugo Good Archive Page</title><link>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/bookmarks/hugo-good-archive-page/</link><pubDate>Sat, 07 Aug 2021 09:39:45 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/bookmarks/hugo-good-archive-page/</guid><description>&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s good archive page style, save time and easy navigation for website. Intent is to make archive page like this.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hugo the Scope the Context and the Dot</title><link>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/bookmarks/hugo-the-scope-the-context-and-the-dot/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2020 18:54:04 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/bookmarks/hugo-the-scope-the-context-and-the-dot/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Hugo Tags List</title><link>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/posts/hugo-tags-list/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2020 18:09:46 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://kbs.murarisumit.in/posts/hugo-tags-list/</guid><description>&lt;p>A simple snippet found to fetch all tags, and still to read it up&lt;/p>
